Description: Dutch Ships and Sailors brings together four Dutch maritime historical datasets. The datasets are modeled as Linked Data- with internal and external links and a schema mapping to a common DSS schema. The four RDF datasets are:1. The Northern Monsterrollen databases- which contain elaborate data on the crew composition of ships from the Northern Netherlands (c. 1800-1930) and provide information on the sailors involved-such as the places of origin- wage and age.2. The VOC Opvarenden database- providing extensive data on crews of VOC ships leaving the Dutch Republic.3. The Dutch-Asiatic Shipping (DAS) database- providing data on all inter-continental voyages of VOC ships.4. The Generale Zeemonsterrollen (GZM) database- providing data on the crew composition and sometimes location of VOC ships stationed in Asia and not engaged in inter-continental shipping.
